  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Seal the duck legs</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat the oven to 160&ordm;C/ 140&ordm;C (fan)/ 350&ordm;F/ Gas 4.</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat.</p>\r\n<p>Once very hot, add the<strong> duck legs</strong> with a generous pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 4-5 minutes or until browned all over.</p>\r\n<p>Once browned, transfer the <strong>duck</strong> to a plate and reserve the pan.</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare the onion and shallots</strong></p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice the&nbsp;<strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Peel and halve the&nbsp;<strong>shallots</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle.</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Caramelise the mushrooms</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discard some of the <strong>fat</strong> from the pan so you're left with just 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>. Return it to a medium heat.</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the&nbsp;<strong>diced onion</strong>&nbsp;and<strong>&nbsp;chestnut mushrooms&nbsp;</strong>and cook for 5-6 minutes or until beginning to soften and caramelise.</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the&nbsp;<strong>chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<strong>Just Add Wine sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;in 400ml&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong>.</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1584.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare your stew for the oven</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once caramelised, add 1 tbsp&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>flour</strong>&nbsp;to the&nbsp;<strong>onion&nbsp;</strong>and<strong>&nbsp;mushrooms</strong>,&nbsp;give everything a good mix up and cook for 1-2 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>Gradually add the <strong>wine stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 minute or until combined.</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> duck legs</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with the <strong>shallots</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>bay leaves</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Pour the&nbsp;wine braise&nbsp;all over and cover the dish tightly with <strong>tin foil</strong> (or a matching lid).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
